@Reasoning:
Top-level entry point. Builds a list of all six suite handles, runs
each suite dispatcher, then prints aggregated results and returns
the all-suites-passed signal.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. Create empty suites_list.
2. For each of lexer/parser/translator/backend/round_trip/integration:
   call run_<phase>_tests, append to suites_list.
3. print_test_results(suites_list).
4. Return check_all_passed(suites_list).
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- All 6 suites pass -> returns 1
- Any suite has failures -> returns 0
@End TestCases

Process called "run_all_tests" that takes nothing returns Integer:
    Let all_suites be proc create_list from ListCore

    Let lexer_suite be proc run_lexer_tests
    proc add_to_list from ListCore with all_suites, lexer_suite

    Let parser_suite be proc run_parser_tests
    proc add_to_list from ListCore with all_suites, parser_suite

    Let translator_suite be proc run_translator_tests
    proc add_to_list from ListCore with all_suites, translator_suite

    Let backend_suite be proc run_backend_tests
    proc add_to_list from ListCore with all_suites, backend_suite

    Let round_trip_suite be proc run_round_trip_tests
    proc add_to_list from ListCore with all_suites, round_trip_suite

    Let integration_suite be proc run_integration_tests
    proc add_to_list from ListCore with all_suites, integration_suite

    proc print_test_results from all_suites

    Return proc check_all_passed from all_suites
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Test Result Reporting
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Iterates suites_list and prints per-suite pass/fail counts plus
totals. Failed tests are enumerated via print_failed_tests.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
For Each suite_ptr in suites_list: read name, passed_count,
failed_count; print "Suite <name>: <p> passed, <f> failed"; on
any failure call print_failed_tests(suite_ptr).
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_results" that takes suites_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Let suite_count be proc get_list_size from ListCore with suites_list
    Let total_passed be 0
    Let total_failed be 0

    Let index be 0
    While index is less than suite_count:
        Let suite_ptr be proc get_from_list from ListCore with suites_list, index

        Let suite_name be proc read_string from Memory with suite_ptr, 0
        Let passed_count be proc read_integer from Memory with suite_ptr, 16
        Let failed_count be proc read_integer from Memory with suite_ptr, 24

        proc print_string from StringCore with "========================================\n"
        proc print_string from StringCore with suite_name
        proc print_string from StringCore with "\n========================================\n"
        proc print_string from StringCore with "Passed: "
        proc print_integer from StringCore with passed_count
        proc print_string from StringCore with "\nFailed: "
        proc print_integer from StringCore with failed_count
        proc print_string from StringCore with "\n\n"

        If failed_count is greater than 0:
            proc print_failed_tests from suite_ptr
        End If

        Set total_passed to total_passed plus passed_count
        Set total_failed to total_failed plus failed_count

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc print_string from StringCore with "========================================\n"
    proc print_string from StringCore with "OVERALL RESULTS\n"
    proc print_string from StringCore with "========================================\n"
    proc print_string from StringCore with "Total Passed: "
    proc print_integer from StringCore with total_passed
    proc print_string from StringCore with "\nTotal Failed: "
    proc print_integer from StringCore with total_failed
    proc print_string from StringCore with "\n"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Walks one suite's tests list and prints details for any TestResult
where passed != 1. Useful for CI consumers who want failure detail
inline.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Read tests_list pointer at offset 8. For Each result_ptr: read
passed at offset 8; if 0 print "FAILED: <name>: <message>".
@End Implementation

Process called "print_failed_tests" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let tests_list be proc read_integer from Memory with suite_ptr, 8
    Let test_count be proc get_list_size from ListCore with tests_list

    proc print_string from StringCore with "Failed Tests:\n"

    Let index be 0
    While index is less than test_count:
        Let test_ptr be proc get_from_list from ListCore with tests_list, index

        Let passed be proc read_integer from Memory with test_ptr, 8

        If passed is equal to 0:
            Let test_name be proc read_string from Memory with test_ptr, 0
            Let message be proc read_string from Memory with test_ptr, 16

            proc print_string from StringCore with "  - "
            proc print_string from StringCore with test_name
            proc print_string from StringCore with "\n    "
            proc print_string from StringCore with message
            proc print_string from StringCore with "\n"
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sums up all suite failed_counts. Returns 1 iff every suite has
zero failures.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
For Each suite_ptr in suites_list: read failed_count at offset 24.
If any > 0 return 0. After loop, return 1.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- All suites failed_count == 0 -> return 1
- Any suite has failed_count > 0 -> return 0
@End TestCases

Process called "check_all_passed" that takes suites_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Let suite_count be proc get_list_size from ListCore with suites_list

    Let index be 0
    While index is less than suite_count:
        Let suite_ptr be proc get_from_list from ListCore with suites_list, index

        Let failed_count be proc read_integer from Memory with suite_ptr, 24

        If failed_count is greater than 0:
            Return 0
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

